The Author
==========

   I, Brian Aagaard Petersen, has written most of the program. The
IFF-save routines were taken from the "newiff.lha" package on Aminet,
the ARexx scripts were written by C. David Shaffer and the
AFM-fileparser is copyrighted Manuel Lemos. It also uses @{"MUI" Link "MUI"}.

   My email adress for those who is able to send mail on internet is:

   aagaard@fys.ku.dk

   and if you are not so fortunate, my snailmail adress is:

   Brian Petersen Brydes Alle 23, room 434 2300 Copenhagen S Denmark

   All email will certainly be answered, but with snailmail it might
take some time.


@EndNode

@Node "WWW-Page" "EqEd.guide/WWW-Page"
@Next "MUI"
@Prev "The Author"
@Toc "Main"

WWW-page
========

   I have created a World-Wide-Web page for EqEd, where you can get
some information on EqEd, for instance what I'm currently working on.
It is also possible to get the latest version almost fresh from the
compiler, since I'll make all intermeadiate versions of EqEd available,
which seems stable. I plan on updating the version at least once a week!
Note that using these versions of EqEd can be a bit risky, as they
hasn't been through anykind of testing at all.

   The address is "http://www.fys.ku.dk/~aagaard/EqEd.html"


@EndNode

