MUI
===

   This application uses

   MUI - MagicUserInterface

   (c) Copyright 1993/94 by Stefan Stuntz

   MUI is a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces.
With the  aid  of  a  preferences program, the user of an application
has the ability to customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

   MUI is distributed as shareware. To obtain a complete package
containing lots of examples and more information about registration
please look for a  file  called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX means the latest
version number) on your local bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

   If you want to register directly, feel free to send

   DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

   to

   Stefan Stuntz

   Eduard-Spranger-Straße 7

   80935 München

   GERMANY

   Note that it is not necessary to register MUI to use EqEd, but you
should consider it, as being able to save change will let EqEd look a
lot nicer.  In my opinion MUI is worth it also without my superb ( :-)
) program!


@EndNode

@Node "Program history" "EqEd.guide/Program history"
@Prev "MUI"
@Toc "Main"

Program history
===============

   This describes the changes made to EqEd between the different
releases:

   ------------------------------------------------------------------
EqEd v0.97

   New features:

   * Implemented MUI3.x standard menus.

   * Userdefinable toolbar is now set by drag and drop.

   * Changed the innerworkings of tool windows - EqEd should open a bit
     quicker on slower machines now.

   * It is finally possible to abort a fontcache rendering.

   * Postscript fonts can be included in EPS files.

   * Bubble help is now implemented.

   Updated:

   * EqEd now uses scrollbars in the window border.

   * EqEd will redirect keystrokes from toolwindow to main window.

   * Changed menu to "Clear" and "Load"

   * The list of packers in preferences can now be resized.

   * Now using Poppen objects to choose colors.

   Bug fixes:

   * Fixed "Disk Full" bug, when using non-type 1 fonts.

   * Cycling between gadgets in prefs improved.

   * Crashed on quit, if EqEd was renamed or icon was missing.

   * Rexx scripts wasn't updated in the menu.

   * indiices are placed lower after a scalable bracket.

   ------------------------------------------------------------------
EqEd v0.96

   New features:

   * Adding, moving and removing tabs, while pressing the CTRL-key,
     will let the change effect the whole coloumn, not just the rows
     below the cursor.

   * Moving tabs while pressing one of the two SHIFT-keys, will make
     all the tabs to the right of moved tabs, move the same distance.
     This may be combined with the CTRL-key.

   * One can now insert ASCII files. This will be more useful, when
     there is better table-support.

   * It is now possible to set the tabs precisely and to load and save
     them. See the menu @{"Edit Tabs" Link "Edit Tabs"}

   * New preference window added. Hopefully this is easier to use.

   * Fontcaches are now kept in memory until memory gets below a
     userdefined limit.

   * Under OS3.0 a memoryhandler will now flush unused caches if the
     system needs more memory.

   * Scalable brackets are now created in a different way. It will no
     longer call type1.library, if a cache is used.

   * Fontsize is no longer set with the PREFS ARexx command, but has
     its own called SetFontSize.

   * Equations now remember the fontsize it was saved in, and will
     change to that when reloaded.

   * It is now possible to create simple tables. This not supported in
     LaTeX though!

   * It is now possible to specify a file to load when EqEd is started
     from the shell i.g. "EqEd docs:Maxwell.eps".

   * Added install script.

   * When preferences are saved, EqEd will remember the directory where
     equations are saved.

   Updated:

   * EqEd now uses its own icon, when iconifi'ed

   * The "EqEd.config" file is now loaded from PROGDIR:

   * The cursorkeys has been redefined, so that holding SHIFT down will
     mark the characters and fast movement is accomplished by holding
     down CTRL and ALT.

   * The tab window will now also use centimeters, if it is selected in
     preference window.

   * New Magic Workbench icons by Trevor Morris.

   * Unscaled brackets is now displayed in the Symbol font, so that they
     are the same as the scaled ones.

   * New improved ARexx scripts

   * The New menu now has Amiga-Z as short cut.

   * Corrected an error in the Postscript output, which caused some
     characters to be placed too close.

   * Tabs placed to the right of outermost tabstop, will now be placed
     at half an inch intervals.

   * Reversed function of CTRL key when placing tab stops. Now you have
     to press the ctrl key, when you wish to split the the tabstops.

   * Changed format of config file, so that feature version of EqEd
     should alway be able to read it.

   * It is possible to place the selection of linewidth on a key, but
     currently not on one of the userdefinable buttons.

   * Made a new tab type for making tables.

   Bug fixes:

   * Corrected two enforcer hits in scalable brackets code.

   * Fraction lines should now be more centered.

   * Corrected error in fontsize, when creating roots in a mark part of
     the equation.

   * The fontsize was wrong, when not using a cache.

   * Fixed major bug in memoryhandler.

   * Fixed bug when moving tab stop in a line containing only that tab
     stop.

   * Boundingbox values are now integers as they should be according to
     the EPS standard.

   ------------------------------------------------------------------

   EqEd v0.95

   New features:

   * The glyphs doesn't overlap anymore. I believe the output is more
     like LaTeX now, but tell me what you think.

   * Rulers implemented. They are fontsensitiv, just change the fixed
     font in MUI-prefs.

   * The vertical ruler now contains some thick lines to mark the lines
     of the Equations. Drag these with the mouse to get more
     linespacing! This works for matrices as well!

   * Tabular handling changed to be done the same way as in
     wordprocessors. This isn't fully supported in LaTeX.

   * Rulers can now be displayed in centimetre's instead of inches.

   * Matrix function now implemented. See the toolwindow with fractions
     etc. Not fully supported in LaTeX.

   * Added menus to copy, paste and clear tabs in rulers.

   * Added ARexx command "Prefs" to allow changing fontsize, resolution
     and cachefile.

   * It is now possible to save parts of an equation. Simply mark it
     and select one of the save menus.

   Updated:

   * Rewritting the window setup routine reduced size of EqEd with 50kb.

   * Made Fontsize gadget in preference window a character wider.

   * EqEd now quits quietly, if the window is empty.

   * Scalable brackets is now at least as big as the unscaled.

   * The display window now scrolls when marking blocks with the mouse
     and moving it beyond the borders.

   * Made mode gadget have "Math" written in italics.

   * Improved the cursor placement with the mouse a tiny bit.

   * The ARexx command SAVE now return the boundingbox information and
     the distance in points to the first baseline from the top of
     equation. This is used in the improved ARexx script.

   * Tabs not on the main line, will now move 1/4 of an inch, instead of
     not being really supported except, by copying them with the help
     of blocks.

   Bug Fixes:

   * Fixed bug in LaTeX output, when it had several lines.

   * Scalable brackets has a more correct height now, and is placed
     better.

   * Scrollbars can now show the entire area.

   * Fixed problem for people, who don't have a "envarc:mui/" directory.

   * mode gadget contained an unnecesary space in Bold Mode text.

   * AREXX command "SetOutput NATIVE" didn' work.

   * EqEd couldn't load the embedded equation in postscript files with
     preview image.

   * Fixed bug in the window scrolling when marking blocks with the
     mouse.

   * Made the PostScript output a bit wider to avoid cutting of j and
     such symbols.

   * Fixed a bug with big greek letters.

   * The little integralsymbol wasn't displayed in the user toolbar.

   ------------------------------------------------------------------
EqEd v0.94

   New features:

   * The height of characters is no longer fixed so vector lines and
     such is placed better.

   * Fonts are now rendered with font engines, eg. Bullet.library and
     Type1.library by Amish S. Dave.

   * Fontcaches are no longer needed, EqEd can render glyphs as needed,
     but it is slower - especially useful when testing different fonts
     and resolutions!

   * It is now possible to include an extra font, which can contain
     symbols not available in the symbols or standard font.

   * Now uses AFM-files, when generating PostScript files. Thanks to
     Manuel Lemos for the code used.

   * First time a symbol window is ever opened, it is placed under the
     mouse.

   * Added ARexx command "EQEDTOFRONT" which brings the screen with
     EqEd to the front.

   * Added Select All menu.

   * Added four menus to globally set the Fast Close menu and layout.

   * Changed Output format to have a special "Embed" menu to support
     Embedding native format in postscript files.

   * Native format can now be included in PostScript and Postscript with
     preview, so you can reload the files.

   * Five ARexx scripts can now be installed in the menu and executed
     from there or with F1-F5.

   * Added window with helpful information, which is displayed when no
     valid configuration file is found.

   Updated:

   * When a vectorarrow is more than one character long, it now is done
     with a \overrightarrow instead of \vec in LaTeX output.

   * Now LaTeX output uses $$ instead of \[ and \].

   * Using the ARexx command Show on EqEd makes it pop its window up
     front - useful when calling EqEd from wordprocessor.

   * EqEd can now run without ARexx.

   * LaTeX now uses eqnarray instead of array, when there is less than 4
     columns, and just $$ if there is one coloumn. Makes the output
     look a bit nicer.

   * Numbers can be bold now.

   * Filerequesters in preferencewindows now has titles and only shows
     relevant files.

   * Config file is again saved in the directory EqEd was launched from.
     If it cannot find the file when loading config, it will look for
     "Env:EqEd.config"

   * The scrollbars arrows now makes the equation move a bit faster.

   * Made the squareroot a bit smaller - tell me if you want it smaller.

   * Added '|' to the scalable brackets.

   * The integral, product and summation symbols are now centered on
     the line as LaTeX does.

   * EqEd now remembers whether the symbols are placed vertically or
     horizontally.

   * Exponent and indiices no longer supports marking with mouse.

   * Added "therefore" symbol. This is not supported in LaTeX output!

   * Changed "SetOutput" and "GetOutput" commands to support the new
     output format with embedded natives.

   Bug fixes:

   * Enter ASCII window wasn't responding.

   * Display of equations bigger than the window was faulty.

   * Added a few newlines at the end of PostScript files to make it
     print correctly on PostScript printers.

   * "  >" was printed wrongly in postscript.

   * Couldn't overwrite cachefiles.

   * Too low stack was causing problems - now the stack will always be
     at least 8kb

   * Saving postscript to a locked file or similar would make EqEd hang.

   * Fixed placement of scalable brackets in PostScript output.

   * Fixed bug in postscriptoutput, which caused problems with placement
     of characters in small sizes.

   ------------------------------------------------------------------

   EqEd v0.93

   New features:

   * Changed task priority to -1 when rendering fonts. Now one can make
     something else while it is rendering. Be careful not to use all
     the memory though, as that will probably make it crash!

   * Made pointer buzy when saving, so you can see when it is finished.

   * Added possibility to pack fontcache if XPK is installed.

   * Added menu to symbol windows, to allow switching between
     horizontal and vertical layout of symbols.

   * Saving preferences will also save window positions and which
     windows are open.

   * The main windows title now displays the name of the equation.

   * Entering a fraction, root, ... while a block is marked will move
     the block on top of the fraction or whatever was pressed.

   * Made it possible to enter characters by their ASCII value.

   * ARexx scripts can now be launched from EqEd.

   * Added a few ARexx commands to allow easy insertion of equations in
     other programs. See @{"ARexx" Link "ARexx"} for details.

   * Made an ARexx script for insertion in FinalWriter and a script to
     launch EqEd.

   * Added menu to symbol windows, which can make the window close
     after a symbol has ben selected.

   * Userdefinable toolbar. Now you can define 8 symbols to be
     available in the main window.

   * Made simple window to change the colors of the equation on the
     screen.  A fancy colorpanel will have to wait.

   * Added Overline, Vector arrows and more. Some of them need to be
     improved.

   Updated:

   * Added function similar to a fraction, but without the diving line.

   * Added limitarrow.

   * Changed "Set Resolution" into "Set Prefs" and made major changes to
     the fontcachehandling. Now the fonts need to be cached, but there
     is greater flexability. You can have caches of different
     resolutions/fontsizes.  Fonts can be named anything.

   * Change the fonts used in the program instead of using the
     FontNames file.

   * Change the fontnames for use in postscriptoutput. It used to have
     the Times font hardcoded!

   * Changed functions popup into window with a listview.

   * The symbols was divided into more groups and there is now two
     lines of symbol "popup" buttons.

   * Added some more symbols.

   * Added lower limit to the "logical and" and the "logical or".

   * Added windows with the greek letters.

   * Added larger versions of a few symbols.

   * Selecting new will reset the filename, so you don't accidently
     overwrite the old file.

   * Trying to open a file which isn't an equation will no longer
     change the filename.

   * Moved configfile to "EnvArc:"

   * Added "..." to menus which open requesters.

   Bugfixes:

   * Removed the flickering while using scrollbars - it was caused by
     using MADF_DRAWOBJECT instead of MADF_DRAWUPDATE. The first causes
     MUI to clear the object area before calling the redraw routine.

   * Removed a Enforcer hit when clicking in displayarea.

   * Removed several Enforcer hits when entering characters at the of a
     line.

   * Made sure the top of extra high letters wasn't cut off.

   * Changed symbolgadgets, so that subset and proper subset are
     different.

   * Forgot to remove a tempfile when saving postscriptpreview.

   * Fixed the bad preview+eps output. I wonder why I didn't discover
     this one - statistically every second outputpicture should be wrong
     before the fix!

   * Changing fontsize sometimes gave an error in LaTeX output.

   * Made sure summation limits and such are placed correctly.

   * Trying to load a nonexistent file would cause EqEd to quit.

   * Removed crash when deleting, cutting and copying certain blocks.

   * Saving files with native code several times would make them bigger
     and bigger and ...

   ------------------------------------------------------------------

   EqEd v0.92 released 20. December 1994 - Betaversion, public release

   New features:

   * Added possible previewimage to postscript output - uses
     printerfonts!!!

   * Parenthesis can be set around a marked block just by hitting the
     right gadget.

   * Added a non-magicwb gadget - it was made by David Kinder.

   * Marked blocks gets deleted if something is entered or
     delete/backspace is pressed.

   Updated:

   * Made special symbols like ©,®... work in postscriptoutput.

   * Made some speciel symbols work in LaTeX-output.

   * Replaced bulletsymbol with a centered dot.

   * Added "logical and" and "logical or" to the symbols.

   * Finished the scalable parenthesises.

   * Added more combinations of parenthesises.

   * Removed a lot of spaces from LaTeX output

   * Changed a few shortcut keys.

   * Made the parenthesis gadgets a bit prettier - now you can see what
     they represents.

   Bugfixes:

   * Fixed blockmarkingerror when a key was pressed while holding down
     the left mousebutton.

   * Fixed displayerror. I got reports that some times the first
     character would disappear, but I couldn't reproduce the error. It
     turned out to be a blitter problem, which I didn't have since I
     use the program cpuclr. A strategic WaitBlit() fixed this (I hope).

   * Made filerequesters open on the same screen as EqEd is running on.

   * Corrected a few spelling errors.

   ------------------------------------------------------------------

   EqEd v0.91 released mid December 1994 - betaversion, public release

   New features:

   * Added progress indicator to fontrenderer - now you know the
     machine is working.

   * Added Set resolution and cachesave when starting without a
     config-file.

   Updated:

   Bugfixes:

   * Fixed placement of symbol limits.

   * Changed the background of symbols to colour 0.  Now the symbols
     doesn't disappear with some MUI-settings.

   * Hardcoded the background of editing area to be SHINE.

   * Fixed error in LaTeX output of scalable parenthesises.

   * Changed nativeformat a bit - the old gave errors in LaTeX-output.

   * Fixed placement of cursor at end of scalable parenthesis.

   * Fixed display error when line began with empty exponent/index.

   ------------------------------------------------------------------

   EqEd v0.90 released beginning of December 1994 - betaversion
internal release

   New features:

   * Editing window scrolls when cursor reaches border.

   * Added scalable parenthesis - not finished yet.

   * Added movement to shift-up/down and alt-left/right.

   * Postscript output.

   * Use adobe type 1 fonts instead of intellifont. This increased
     requirements considerably, but allowed postscript output and
     speedimprovement.

   * Added fontcache to avoid waiting on the fontrender.

   * Added online help. Pressing help on gadget or menu brings up this
     manual.

   * Added a real manual.

   Updated:

   * Fractions, roots and exponents moved from hardcoded key to toolbar.

   * Set key expanded to include functions and keys.

   * Added menu which allows to change the line size.

   * Toolbar symbols was implemented as pictures instead of font.

   * Removed bold italics mode.

   * Changes resolution window. Now screenresolution is entered in DPI.
     It can now look nice on both hires and medres screens.

   * Linesizes in roots and fractions scales with the resolution.

   * Moved exponents up a bit.

   Bugfixes:

   * Mouse can now place cursor at the rightmost character in a root.

   * Fixed LaTeX output errors with specialsymbols as $ \ ...

   * Removed serious bug in Cut function.

   * Might have fixed enforcer hit from functions-popup (I have an
     68EC030 so I cannot check)

   ------------------------------------------------------------------

   EqEd first release had version 1.0 at someplaces and 0.5 at others.
This was an fault has changed. It was released October 1994 as preview
version to a few people. Things changing before this wasn't written
down!

@EndNode

